promptInjection:
Use these pre-built SVG chart patterns for ALL data viz. DO NOT pull in Chart.js, D3, or any external chart library — the patterns below cover 90% of dashboard needs in <2KB of SVG.

**STAT CARD** (single big number + label + delta — the dashboard atom):
```html
<div class="stat-card">
  <div class="stat-label">Active Users</div>
  <div class="stat-value">12,834</div>
  <div class="stat-delta up">↑ 8.2% vs last week</div>
</div>
```
```css
.stat-card { background: var(--surface, #1e293b); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--border, #334155); }
.stat-label { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted, #94a3b8); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.stat-value { font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; color: var(--text, #f1f5f9); line-height: 1.1; }
.stat-delta { font-size: 13px; margin-top: 6px; font-weight: 500; }
.stat-delta.up { color: #22c55e; }
.stat-delta.down { color: #ef4444; }
.stat-delta.flat { color: var(--text-muted, #94a3b8); }
```

**SPARKLINE** (tiny inline trend line — pair with a stat card):
```html
<svg class="sparkline" viewBox="0 0 100 30" preserveAspectRatio="none" width="120" height="32">
  <polyline fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" points="0,25 10,22 20,18 30,20 40,15 50,12 60,14 70,10 80,8 90,5 100,3"/>
</svg>
```
JS helper to map data → points:
```javascript
function sparklinePoints(values, w = 100, h = 30) {
  const max = Math.max(...values), min = Math.min(...values);
  const range = max - min || 1;
  const step = w / (values.length - 1 || 1);
  return values.map((v, i) => `${i * step},${h - ((v - min) / range) * h}`).join(' ');
}
// <polyline points={sparklinePoints([4,8,3,9,12,7,15])} />
```

