**RULES:**
- Always use `viewBox` for charts so they scale; set `width="100%"` for fluid layouts.
- Use `currentColor` for grid/axis lines so the chart inherits the parent's text color (theme-aware).
- Number values use `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;` so digits don't shift width when changing.
- Color tokens: prefer `var(--accent)` over hard-coded blue so the chart uses the app's theme.
- For a sparse dashboard, use a 12-column CSS Grid: `.dash-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr); gap: 16px; }` and let stat cards span 3-4 columns each.
- DO NOT pull in Chart.js / D3 / Recharts — these snippets cover the 90% case in <2KB.
